    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-10-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-10-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="770"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d770">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Eddy</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-10-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 17, 1904</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 157.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In connection with the Department’s instruction
                    No. 155, of the 13th instant, I inclose a bulletin of verification issued under
                    date of the 9th ultimo by the Japanese office at Nagasaki, addressed to the
                    office of San Francisco,<note n="a" xml:id="d770fna">Not printed.</note>
                    reporting the opening and resealing by the Russian post-office at Vladivostok of
                    a sack made up at the office of San Francisco, addressed to the U. S. S. <hi
                        rend="italic">Cincinnati</hi> and dispatched per the steamer <hi
                        rend="italic">Calchas.</hi>
                </p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
